### Problem Description

Converting a histogram to tdigest in a stats command fails with a validation exception, while doing the same conversion as a separate eval works correctly.

### Steps to Reproduce

```
PUT /test
{
	"settings": {
		"mode": "time_series",
		"routing_path": "host"
	},

	"mappings": {
		"properties": {
			"@timestamp" : {
				"type": "date"
			},
			"host": {
				"type": "keyword",
				"time_series_dimension": true
			},
			"hist": {
				"type": "histogram"
			},
			"hist_metric": {
				"type": "histogram",
				"time_series_metric": "histogram"
			}
		}
	}
}

POST /test/_doc
{
	"@timestamp": "2026-01-14T00:01:02",
	"host": "foo",
	"hist":{"values": [1, 2], "counts":[13, 17]},
	"hist_metric":{"values": [1, 2], "counts":[13, 17]}
}


// This fails showing the error
POST /_query?format=txt
{
	"query": "TS test | STATS AVG(to_tdigest(hist_metric))"
}

// This query, which should be equivalent to the above query, works
POST /_query?format=txt
{
	"query": "TS test | EVAL td = to_tdigest(hist_metric) | STATS AVG(td)"
}
```

The error message from the failure:
```{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [
      {
        "type": "verification_exception",
        "reason": "Found 1 problem\nline 1:32: argument of [implicit time-series aggregation function (HistogramMergeOverTime) for hist_metric] must be [exponential_histogram or tdigest], found value [hist_metric] type [histogram]; to aggregate non-numeric fields, use the FROM command instead of the TS command"
      }
    ],
    "type": "verification_exception",
    "reason": "Found 1 problem\nline 1:32: argument of [implicit time-series aggregation function (HistogramMergeOverTime) for hist_metric] must be [exponential_histogram or tdigest], found value [hist_metric] type [histogram]; to aggregate non-numeric fields, use the FROM command instead of the TS command"
  },
  "status": 400
}
```

